docstring:
This function finds and returns all automorphic numbers within a specified range, inclusive.
An automorphic number is a number whose square ends in the same digits as the number itself.
The function takes two integers as input: start and endVal, representing the range to search for automorphic numbers.

Examples:
>>> FindAutomorphicNumbers(1, 10)
{1, 5, 6}
>>> FindAutomorphicNumbers(1, 25)
{1, 5, 6, 25}
>>> FindAutomorphicNumbers(50, 100)
{}
>>> FindAutomorphicNumbers(1, 5)
{1, 5}

